[Mr. Frank Rhodehamel&rsquo;s random lecture notes, most of which seem to pertain to chapter two of the Bhagavad-Gitā]
&ldquo;Spirituality can never be attained until materiality is gone.&rdquo;
The first discourse in the Gita can be taken allegorically.
&ldquo;The Vedas only teach of things in nature, only teach of nature.&rdquo;
We are always letting sentiment usurp the place of duty, and flattering ourselves that we are acting in response to true love.
